subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. This species differs from other species of the genus by the following character states: 
1
) head narrowed behind eyes, 
2
) yellow spots on orbits near antennal sockets and on top of eyes, 
3
) rounded apical margin of clypeus, 
3
) occipital carina complete, 
4
) open areolet, 
5
) propodeum with only area petiolaris obliterated anteriorly, 
6
) ovipositor as long as first metasomal tergite, without nodus, with subapical dorsal notch and lower valve without teeth at apex.
